race.comment: ARUGAMAMA (12) was good here fresh in a key lead-up and now meets them with a significant 4kg swing at the weights. She's produced her best figures once she gets out to these genuine staying journeys and looks perfectly placed to add a black-type win to the résumé. BOLD SOUL (1) has been giving himself too much to do all prep, but he's got the miles in the legs now and is a proven operator at this level. If Noonan can have him rolling before the corner, he'll take plenty of stopping. KOMACHI (2) has really found her groove over staying trips and continues to elevate. This is her first crack at a journey of this depth, but if they roll forward again, she'll give herself every chance. CRIMSON VINE (14) has returned to somewhere near her best in her past two and should be hitting her straps for what is clearly a target race. Don't dismiss. MR WATERVILLE (4) closed strongly to just miss at Colac and the rise in trip is a big tick. Pannell will need to be sharp from the wide draw.
